The fragrance packaging market is segmented based on material type, product type, and end-use. In terms of material type, glass packaging is widely used in the fragrance industry for its premium look and ability to preserve the scent effectively. Plastic packaging, on the other hand, is popular for its affordability and versatility in design. Metal packaging is known for its durability and ability to provide a luxurious feel to the product. When it comes to product type, bottles are the most common packaging form for fragrances, followed by caps & closures and labels & wraps. In terms of end-use, fragrances are categorized for men, women, or unisex, leading to different packaging designs to cater to each target demographic.

